<subSubSection id="9F9C21FE9D19A66846C0923CFDD7FB5C" pageId="3" pageNumber="197" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D73972759D19A66846C0923CFDD7FB5C" blockId="3.[151,1437,1017,2019]" pageId="3" pageNumber="197">
<emphasis id="E5F2AE679D19A66846C0923CFE23FB30" bold="true" box="[199,421,1130,1155]" pageId="3" pageNumber="197">Diagnosis of male.</emphasis>
The new species is distinct among its Palaearctic congeners by possessing enlarged and flattened pedicel in the male, which is about four times as long as antennomere III. When combined with the frontal modifications (
<figureCitation id="4FBD6EF09D19A668474792E4FE04FB79" box="[320,386,1202,1227]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[207,1382,193,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[207,1383,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Diagnostic features of Batrisodes petalosus (A, C – G. Male. B, H – J. Female). A, B. Head, in dorsal view. C. Antenna. D. Mesofemur. E. Mesotibia. F. Aedeagus, in ventral view. G. Same, in lateral view. H. Tergite VIII. I. Sternite VIII. J. Genital complex. Scales: A – G = 0.2 mm; H – J = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/192963/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="197">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
A) and aedeagus (median lobe apically expanded; 
<figureCitation id="4FBD6EF09D19A66845B492E4FC73FB79" box="[947,1013,1202,1227]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[207,1382,193,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[207,1383,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Diagnostic features of Batrisodes petalosus (A, C – G. Male. B, H – J. Female). A, B. Head, in dorsal view. C. Antenna. D. Mesofemur. E. Mesotibia. F. Aedeagus, in ventral view. G. Same, in lateral view. H. Tergite VIII. I. Sternite VIII. J. Genital complex. Scales: A – G = 0.2 mm; H – J = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/192963/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="197">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
F), it can be readily separated from all other European and East Asian species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9F9C21FE9D19A66846C092ACFAA9F80D" pageId="3" pageNumber="197" type="description">
<paragraph id="D73972759D19A66846C092ACFE93F8B8" blockId="3.[151,1437,1017,2019]" pageId="3" pageNumber="197">
<emphasis id="E5F2AE679D19A66846C092ACFEDFFAA0" bold="true" box="[199,345,1274,1299]" pageId="3" pageNumber="197">Description.</emphasis>
Male (
<figureCitation id="4FBD6EF09D19A66847B592ACFE7CFAA1" box="[434,506,1274,1299]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1571,1593]" captionTargetBox="[171,1420,320,1536]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,303,1548]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Dorsal habitus of Batrisodes petalosus. A. Male; B. Female. Scale: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/192962/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="197">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
A). Body reddish brown, BL 
<quantity id="107EDF909D19A668455992ACFB8FFAA1" box="[862,1033,1274,1299]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.88" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="2.86" pageId="3" pageNumber="197" unit="mm" value="2.88" valueMax="2.9" valueMin="2.86">2.86–2.90 mm</quantity>
. Head (
<figureCitation id="4FBD6EF09D19A668426E92ACFB36FAA1" box="[1129,1200,1274,1299]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[207,1382,193,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[207,1383,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Diagnostic features of Batrisodes petalosus (A, C – G. Male. B, H – J. Female). A, B. Head, in dorsal view. C. Antenna. D. Mesofemur. E. Mesotibia. F. Aedeagus, in ventral view. G. Same, in lateral view. H. Tergite VIII. I. Sternite VIII. J. Genital complex. Scales: A – G = 0.2 mm; H – J = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/192963/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="197">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
A) wider than long, roundly rectangular, HL 
<quantity id="107EDF909D19A66847AB9348FDD6FA85" box="[428,592,1310,1335]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.3" metricValueMax="6.5" metricValueMin="6.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="197" unit="mm" value="0.63" valueMax="0.65" valueMin="0.61">0.61–0.65 mm</quantity>
, HW 
<quantity id="107EDF909D19A66844969348FCB0FA85" box="[657,822,1310,1335]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.8500000000000005" metricValueMax="6.8999999999999995" metricValueMin="6.800000000000001" pageId="3" pageNumber="197" unit="mm" value="0.685" valueMax="0.69" valueMin="0.68">0.68–0.69 mm</quantity>
, with distinct, nude vertexal foveae, antennal tubercles prominent; anterior margin of frons strongly sinuate, with five bunches of thick setae anteromedially, area between antennal tubercles concave; clypeus medially impunctate, with round anterior margin; short lateral longitudinal carinae extending from level of vertexal foveae posteriorly to occipital constriction, lacking median vertexal carina. Each eye composed of about 50 facets. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="4FBD6EF09D19A668451F93F8FCDAFA74" box="[792,860,1454,1479]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[207,1382,193,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[207,1383,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Diagnostic features of Batrisodes petalosus (A, C – G. Male. B, H – J. Female). A, B. Head, in dorsal view. C. Antenna. D. Mesofemur. E. Mesotibia. F. Aedeagus, in ventral view. G. Same, in lateral view. H. Tergite VIII. I. Sternite VIII. J. Genital complex. Scales: A – G = 0.2 mm; H – J = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/192963/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="197">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
C) moniliform, with 11 antennomeres, club formed by three apical antennomeres; scape broad, slightly elongate, pedicel larger than scape, widest at apex. Pronotum about as long as wide, PL 
<quantity id="107EDF909D19A66847C693A0FDE0F9BD" box="[449,614,1526,1551]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.85" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.699999999999999" pageId="3" pageNumber="197" unit="mm" value="0.585" valueMax="0.6" valueMin="0.57">0.57–0.60 mm</quantity>
, PW 
<quantity id="107EDF909D19A66844A393A0FCCFF9BD" box="[676,841,1526,1551]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.15" metricValueMax="6.2" metricValueMin="6.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="197" unit="mm" value="0.615" valueMax="0.62" valueMin="0.61">0.61–0.62 mm</quantity>
, rounded laterally, disc slightly convex, with distinct median antebasal foveae, median and lateral longitudinal sulci present; outer and inner basolateral foveae small but distinct. Elytra slightly wider than long, EL 
<quantity id="107EDF909D19A66844819069FCADF9E5" box="[646,811,1599,1623]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.85" metricValueMax="8.9" metricValueMin="8.8" pageId="3" pageNumber="197" unit="mm" value="0.885" valueMax="0.89" valueMin="0.88">0.88–0.89 mm</quantity>
, EW 
<quantity id="107EDF909D19A668456E9069FB96F9E5" box="[873,1040,1599,1623]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.15" metricValueMax="9.3" metricValueMin="9.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="197" unit="mm" value="0.915" valueMax="0.93" valueMin="0.9">0.90–0.93 mm</quantity>
; each elytron with three large basal foveae; discal striae shallow and short. Mesofemur (
<figureCitation id="4FBD6EF09D19A66844E39034FCA1F9C9" box="[740,807,1634,1659]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[207,1382,193,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[207,1383,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Diagnostic features of Batrisodes petalosus (A, C – G. Male. B, H – J. Female). A, B. Head, in dorsal view. C. Antenna. D. Mesofemur. E. Mesotibia. F. Aedeagus, in ventral view. G. Same, in lateral view. H. Tergite VIII. I. Sternite VIII. J. Genital complex. Scales: A – G = 0.2 mm; H – J = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/192963/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="197">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
D) with tiny ventral spine near middle; mesotibiae (
<figureCitation id="4FBD6EF09D19A66843689034FF23F92C" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[207,1382,193,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[207,1383,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Diagnostic features of Batrisodes petalosus (A, C – G. Male. B, H – J. Female). A, B. Head, in dorsal view. C. Antenna. D. Mesofemur. E. Mesotibia. F. Aedeagus, in ventral view. G. Same, in lateral view. H. Tergite VIII. I. Sternite VIII. J. Genital complex. Scales: A – G = 0.2 mm; H – J = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/192963/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="197">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
E) with small ventral denticle at basal 3/5, and large triangular apical spine. Abdomen wider than long, AL 
<quantity id="107EDF909D19A668435A90D0FE87F971" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.8" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="7.6" pageId="3" pageNumber="197" unit="mm" value="0.78" valueMax="0.8" valueMin="0.76">0.76– 0.80 mm</quantity>
, AW 
<quantity id="107EDF909D19A668474F90FCFE75F971" box="[328,499,1706,1731]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.6" metricValueMax="8.7" metricValueMin="8.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="197" unit="mm" value="0.86" valueMax="0.87" valueMin="0.85">0.85–0.87 mm</quantity>
; tergite IV longest, about twice as long as next, with strongly oblique marginal carinae. Length of aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="4FBD6EF09D19A66847F19098FDB8F954" box="[502,574,1742,1767]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[207,1382,193,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[207,1383,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Diagnostic features of Batrisodes petalosus (A, C – G. Male. B, H – J. Female). A, B. Head, in dorsal view. C. Antenna. D. Mesofemur. E. Mesotibia. F. Aedeagus, in ventral view. G. Same, in lateral view. H. Tergite VIII. I. Sternite VIII. J. Genital complex. Scales: A – G = 0.2 mm; H – J = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/192963/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="197">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
F–G) 
<quantity id="107EDF909D19A66844819098FD74F955" box="[646,754,1742,1767]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="197" unit="mm" value="0.45">0.45 mm</quantity>
; median lobe simple, flattened, apically expanded, nearly symmetric.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D73972759D19A66846C09140FAA9F80D" blockId="3.[151,1437,1017,2019]" pageId="3" pageNumber="197">
Female (
<figureCitation id="4FBD6EF09D19A668472F9140FEEDF89C" box="[296,363,1814,1839]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1571,1593]" captionTargetBox="[171,1420,320,1536]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,303,1548]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Dorsal habitus of Batrisodes petalosus. A. Male; B. Female. Scale: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/192962/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="197">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
B). General habitus similar to male, frons (
<figureCitation id="4FBD6EF09D19A668454E9140FC0AF89C" box="[841,908,1814,1839]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[207,1382,193,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[207,1383,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Diagnostic features of Batrisodes petalosus (A, C – G. Male. B, H – J. Female). A, B. Head, in dorsal view. C. Antenna. D. Mesofemur. E. Mesotibia. F. Aedeagus, in ventral view. G. Same, in lateral view. H. Tergite VIII. I. Sternite VIII. J. Genital complex. Scales: A – G = 0.2 mm; H – J = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/192963/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="197">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
B) unmodified; each eye composed of about 35 facets, and with one short ocular spine; pedicel not dilated as in male, only about twice length of antennomere III; legs lacking denticle and spine; tergite VIII (
<figureCitation id="4FBD6EF09D19A668449A9108FD67F8C4" box="[669,737,1886,1911]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[207,1382,193,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[207,1383,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Diagnostic features of Batrisodes petalosus (A, C – G. Male. B, H – J. Female). A, B. Head, in dorsal view. C. Antenna. D. Mesofemur. E. Mesotibia. F. Aedeagus, in ventral view. G. Same, in lateral view. H. Tergite VIII. I. Sternite VIII. J. Genital complex. Scales: A – G = 0.2 mm; H – J = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/192963/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="197">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
H) semicircular; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="4FBD6EF09D19A66842459108FB0EF8C4" box="[1090,1160,1886,1911]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[207,1382,193,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[207,1383,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Diagnostic features of Batrisodes petalosus (A, C – G. Male. B, H – J. Female). A, B. Head, in dorsal view. C. Antenna. D. Mesofemur. E. Mesotibia. F. Aedeagus, in ventral view. G. Same, in lateral view. H. Tergite VIII. I. Sternite VIII. J. Genital complex. Scales: A – G = 0.2 mm; H – J = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/192963/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="197">
Fig. 
<date id="A33854B59D19A668427E9109FB0EF8C4" box="[1145,1160,1887,1911]" pageId="3" pageNumber="197">4</date>
</figureCitation>
I) transverse; symmetric genital complex (
<figureCitation id="4FBD6EF09D19A668475C91D4FE18F829" box="[347,414,1922,1947]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[207,1382,193,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[207,1383,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Diagnostic features of Batrisodes petalosus (A, C – G. Male. B, H – J. Female). A, B. Head, in dorsal view. C. Antenna. D. Mesofemur. E. Mesotibia. F. Aedeagus, in ventral view. G. Same, in lateral view. H. Tergite VIII. I. Sternite VIII. J. Genital complex. Scales: A – G = 0.2 mm; H – J = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/192963/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="197">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
J) weakly sclerotized, width 
<quantity id="107EDF909D19A66844E791D4FCCEF829" box="[736,840,1922,1946]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="3" pageNumber="197" unit="mm" value="0.27">0.27 mm</quantity>
. Measurements of body parts: BL 
<quantity id="107EDF909D19A66842CB91D4FAB5F829" box="[1228,1331,1922,1947]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.96" pageId="3" pageNumber="197" unit="mm" value="2.96">2.96 mm</quantity>
, HL 
<quantity id="107EDF909D19A668436C91D4FF43F80D" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="197" unit="mm" value="0.62">0.62 mm</quantity>
, HW 
<quantity id="107EDF909D19A668470191F1FEEAF80D" box="[262,364,1959,1983]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.199999999999999" pageId="3" pageNumber="197" unit="mm" value="0.72">0.72 mm</quantity>
, PL 
<quantity id="107EDF909D19A668479891F0FD83F80D" box="[415,517,1958,1983]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="197" unit="mm" value="0.61">0.61 mm</quantity>
, PW 
<quantity id="107EDF909D19A668444591F0FD2EF80D" box="[578,680,1958,1983]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="197" unit="mm" value="0.62">0.62 mm</quantity>
, EL 
<quantity id="107EDF909D19A66844DA91F1FCC5F80D" box="[733,835,1959,1983]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.7" pageId="3" pageNumber="197" unit="mm" value="0.87">0.87 mm</quantity>
, EW 
<quantity id="107EDF909D19A668458691F0FC61F80D" box="[897,999,1958,1983]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.6" pageId="3" pageNumber="197" unit="mm" value="0.96">0.96 mm</quantity>
, AL 
<quantity id="107EDF909D19A668421891F0FB03F80D" box="[1055,1157,1958,1983]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.6" pageId="3" pageNumber="197" unit="mm" value="0.86">0.86 mm</quantity>
, AW 
<quantity id="107EDF909D19A66842C391F1FAADF80D" box="[1220,1323,1959,1983]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="197" unit="mm" value="0.92">0.92 mm</quantity>
.
