<subSubSection id="9F9C21FE9D1EA66F46C096EAFC36FF4B" pageId="4" pageNumber="198" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="D73972759D1EA66F46C096EAFC36FF4B" blockId="4.[151,1436,151,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis id="E5F2AE679D1EA66F46C096EAFEC8FF66" bold="true" box="[199,334,188,213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="198">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Greek adjective ‘petalos’, meaning ‘flat, spread out’, referring to the flattened and enlarged male pedicel of the new species.
</paragraph>
